Sprite catalog provenance
=========================

`catalog.json` in this directory is generated output of the Meetropolis
sprite generator located at `tools/sprite-generator/` (engine.py, poses.py,
generate.py, export_catalog.py and the `catalogs/` package). Those generator
sources carry `SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-only` and stay AGPL-3.0-only.

This generated `catalog.json` is licensed under the MIT License, consistent
with the surrounding `@meetropolis/shared` package (see ../package.json and
../LICENSE). Tiamat UG holds the copyright in both the generator and this
generated output and, as the copyright holder, licenses this file under MIT.
The AGPL-3.0 copyleft binds third parties who run the generator on their own;
it does not constrain the copyright holder's licensing of its own output.

It is vendored here so the shared composer, the AGPL-3.0 server and the web
editor all read one identical contract (guaranteeing preview == the
server-composited sheet).

Do not hand-edit `catalog.json`. Regenerate it from the generator, then
format it so the diff stays minimal:

    cd tools/sprite-generator
    python3 export_catalog.py                          # -> packages/shared/sprite/catalog.json
    cd ../.. && npx prettier --write packages/shared/sprite/catalog.json

All pixel data is authored procedurally from the grid templates in
`tools/sprite-generator/catalogs/`; no third-party pixel data is read,
sampled, or referenced.
